nt","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have weather data for San José, Costa Rica. Let me convert the temperature from Kelvin to Celsius and get the local time. Now let me search for AI engineering\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"1001d39a915b432f9703dcb7933d12cb","name":"composio__COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TOOLS","arguments":{"queries":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6},"session":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}},"partialArgs":"{\"queries\": [{\"use_case\": \"search for latest AI engineering news and tools for TypeScript JavaScript developers\"}], \"session\": {\"id\": \"kids\"}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"online/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v3.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781366436411,"responseId":"gen-1781366436-Jv2iLcH9YFweH39SAY3R"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"1001d39a915b432f9703dcb7933d12cb","toolName":"composio__COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TOOLS","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"data\":{\"results\":[{\"index\":1,\"use_case\":\"search for latest AI engineering news and tools for TypeScript JavaScript developers\",\"execution_guidance\":\"IMPORTANT: Follow the recommended plan below. Extract steps before execution, adapt to your current context, execute sequentially with current_step parameter, and check known pitfalls to avoid errors.\",\"recommended_plan_steps\":[\"[Required] [Prerequisite]: Define focus keywords for AI coding tools (product/vendor names + \\\"release\\\"/\\\"GA\\\"/\\\"SDK\\\") and a day-level time_window/when for recency filtering before COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS.\",\"[Optional (if you need adjacent query ideas)] [Prerequisite]: Generate related keywords using COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TRENDS (expand focus) before running COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS.\",\"[Required] [Step]: Retrieve recent articles using COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS (collect news_results[].title, link, source, published_at, snippet for later ranking/filtering).\",\"[Optional (if results are noisy or coverage is incomplete)] [Next Step]: Re-run COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS with refined/alternate keywords and merge results; de-dupe by link/URL before ranking.\",\"[Optional (if you need grounded details beyond snippets)] [Next Step]: Enrich a small top set of links using COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT (extract full text for grounded summaries/quotes).\",\"[Optional (if strict recency or NEWS inventory is thin)] [Fallback]: Broaden time_window/when and rerun COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS; if still sparse, use COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB to find relevant posts/blogs and optionally enrich key links with COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT.\"],\"known_pitfalls\":[\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS] Results are in response.data.news_results (not response.data.answer); batched runs may nest under results[i].response.data.news_results—extract defensively.\",\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS] published_at may be a string with a trailing \\\" UTC\\\"; normalize to datetime before sorting/filtering (avoid string comparisons).\",\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS] Tight past-day windows can return has_results=false; broaden keywords or relax time_window/when to recover coverage.\",\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS] Broad queries can skew toward press-release wires/off-target items; refine keywords (and expect overlap across reruns)—de-dupe by link/URL.\",\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT] Full-text payloads can be large/truncated inline; rely on returned results objects rather than expecting short snippets.\"],\"reference_workbench_snippets\":[{\"description\":\"Parse a saved batched response and extract all news_results items safely by index\",\"code\":\"```python\\nimport json\\nx=json.load(open(\\\"response.json\\\"))\\nfor r in x.get(\\\"results\\\",[]):\\n  d=r.get(\\\"response\\\",{}).get(\\\"data\\\",{})\\n  for a in d.get(\\\"news_results\\\",[]):\\n    print(a.get(\\\"title\\\"),a.get(\\\"link\\\"),a.get(\\\"published_at\\\"))\\n```\"}],\"difficulty\":\"easy\",\"primary_tool_slugs\":[\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\"],\"related_tool_slugs\":[\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT\",\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB\",\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TRENDS\"],\"toolkits\":[\"composio_search\"],\"plan_id\":\"38ed75c076ab4c92938778ad7adb8b0c\"}],\"toolkit_connection_statuses\":[{\"toolkit\":\"composio_search\",\"description\":\"Composio Search provides comprehensive web search across travel (flights, hotels, events), e-commerce (Amazon, Walmart, shopping), financial markets, news, academic research, images, and location services.\",\"has_active_connection\":true,\"status_message\":\"This toolkit does not require authentication. Tools are ready to use.\"}],\"tool_schemas\":{\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\":{\"toolkit\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH\",\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\",\"description\":\"Search for the latest news articles and current events with smart filtering. Searches news-oriented sources only (not blogs, docs, or company pages). Results nest under `data.results.news_results`; a 200 response with empty `news_results` or `news_results_state: 'Fully empty'` means no results — broaden query or `when` window. Auto-correction (`showing_results_for`) can silently redirect queries; verify returned articles match intended topic. Only first page returned by default; follow `pagination.next` for more pages. Supports 100+ languages and countries. Use advanced operators like 'site:' for publisher filtering directly in your query. Examples: query=\\\"artificial intelligence\\\" + when=\\\"w\\\" for past week's AI news query=\\\"climate change\\\" + gl=\\\"us\\\" + hl=\\\"en\\\" for US climate news query=\\\"business news\\\" + when=\\\"d\\\" for today's business news query=\\\"site:bbc.com tesla\\\" + when=\\\"d\\\" for today's BBC Tesla news\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"gl\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"us\",\"uk\",\"ca\",\"au\",\"de\",\"fr\",\"jp\",\"in\",\"br\",\"mx\"],\"description\":\"Country code for news region (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2). Determines which country's news sources to prioritize.\"},\"hl\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"en\",\"es\",\"fr\",\"de\",\"pt\",\"it\",\"ja\",\"ko\",\"zh-cn\",\"zh-tw\",\"ar\",\"hi\",\"ru\"],\"description\":\"Language code for news interface and results. Most languages use ISO 639-1 codes (e.g., 'en', 'es'). Chinese requires regional variants: 'zh-cn' (Simplified) or 'zh-tw' (Traditional). Standalone 'zh' is normalized to 'zh-cn'.\"},\"when\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"d\",\"w\",\"m\",\"y\"],\"description\":\"Time filter for news articles. 'd' = past day, 'w' = past week, 'm' = past month, 'y' = past year. These are coarse UTC-based buckets with no finer granularity; filter `published_at` client-side for precise ranges. Combining narrow queries with strict `when` filters frequently returns zero results; broaden either before concluding no data exists.\"},\"query\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"artificial intelligence\",\"climate change\",\"site:bbc.com technology\",\"when:7d startup funding\",\"Tesla stock market\",\"COVID-19 vaccine news\"],\"description\":\"Search query for news articles. Supports advanced operators like 'site:', 'when:', etc. Cannot be used with topic_token, publication_token, or story_token.\"},\"start\":{\"type\":\"integer\",\"minimum\":0,\"examples\":[0,10,20,30],\"description\":\"Result offset for pagination. Each page typically contains 10 results. Use multiples of 10 (0, 10, 20, 30, ...) to navigate pages. Stop paginating when a page returns no new results.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT\":{\"toolkit\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH\",\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT\",\"description\":\"Fetch and extract clean, readable page text (markdown) from public web pages (HTML content) using the Exa API. Use when you need to retrieve actual content from search results or documentation links to extract setup steps, requirements, or citations. Only works with web page URLs - does not support direct links to images, PDFs, or other binary files.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"urls\"],\"properties\":{\"text\":{\"type\":\"boolean\",\"default\":true,\"description\":\"Include extracted markdown text content from the page. Defaults to true.\"},\"urls\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"examples\":[[\"https://example.com/article\",\"https://docs.python.org/\"]],\"description\":\"List of public URLs to web pages (HTML content) to fetch content from. URLs must be valid and publicly accessible. Do not use direct links to images (.jpg, .png, .gif), PDFs, or other binary files - use web page URLs only. Also accepts a single URL string.\"},\"extras\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"description\":\"Additional content options like imageLinks or links counts (e.g., {'imageLinks': 3, 'links': 5}).\",\"additionalProperties\":{\"type\":\"integer\"}},\"summary\":{\"anyOf\":[{\"type\":\"boolean\"},{\"type\":\"object\",\"additionalProperties\":{\"type\":\"string\"}}],\"description\":\"Include AI-generated summary of the page content. Can be boolean or object with query/schema options.\"},\"max_characters\":{\"type\":\"integer\",\"description\":\"Maximum number of characters to extract from each page. Maps to text.maxCharacters in Exa API.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB\":{\"toolkit\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH\",\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB\",\"description\":\"Perform a web search using the Exa API. Returns a nested structure: narrative summary under results.answer, sources under results.citations (and optionally results.organic_results). Prioritize results.citations as primary evidence over results.answer, which can be vague. Only indexes publicly available content — no paywalled, login-gated, or private content. No date filters enforced; include recency terms in query and verify dates in snippets manually. Throttle to ~1–2 requests/second; bursty queries trigger HTTP 429. Large responses may be stored remotely — use structure_info to locate results.answer and results.citations.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"query\"],\"properties\":{\"query\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"Coffee\"],\"description\":\"The search query for the Composio Exa API. Must be non-empty; using any other parameter name (e.g., 'q') causes an invalid-request error. Include qualifiers (year, region, platform, intent) for better results — broad queries return generic content; excessive site: or quoted-term filters can return zero results. Add disambiguating terms (city, role, domain) when searching for people or organizations with common names.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TRENDS\":{\"toolkit\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH\",\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TRENDS\",\"description\":\"Discover trending topics, search patterns, and popularity data. Analyzes search interest over time, ...\",\"hasFullSchema\":false,\"schemaRef\":{\"tool\":\"COMPOSIO_GET_TOOL_SCHEMAS\",\"args\":{\"tool_slugs\":[\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TRENDS\"]}}}},\"time_info\":{\"current_time_utc\":\"2026-06-13T16:00:42.286Z\",\"current_time_utc_epoch_seconds\":1781366442,\"message\":\"\\n          - This is time in UTC timezone. Get timezone from user if you needed.\\n          - Always use this time info to construct parameters for tool calls appropriately even when the tool call requires relative times like 'last week', 'last 24 hours', 'today', 'tomorrow' etc.\\n          - Do not hallucinate the time or timezone by yourself.\\n        \"},\"session\":{\"id\":\"kids\",\"generate_id\":false,\"instructions\":\"REQUIRED: Pass session_id \\\"kids\\\" in ALL subsequent meta tool calls for this workflow.\"},\"next_steps_guidance\":[\"1) Connections active, proceed to next step\",\"2) Extract validated plan steps returned above, acknowledge each step, then execute sequentially updating current_step parameter. Check pitfalls during execution.\"],\"success\":true,\"error\":null},\"error\":null,\"log_id\":\"log_bnzBDGU03fqG\",\"successful\":true}"}],"details":{"mcpServer":"composio","mcpTool":"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TOOLS"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781366442330},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me search for recent AI engineering news with a focus on TypeScript/JavaScript tools and\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"f4ce2ddba04b415a8f8f855b09667f6d","name":"composio__COMPOSIO_MULTI_EXECUTE_TOOL","arguments":{"tools":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6},"sync_response_to_workbench":false,"current_step":"SEARCHING_AI_NEWS","current_step_metric":"1/1 search","thought":"Search for AI engineering tools news for JavaScript/TypeScript developers","session_id":"kids"},"partialArgs":"{\"tools\": [{\"tool_slug\": \"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\", \"arguments\": {\"query\": \"TypeScript JavaScript AI tools SDK libraries frontend developers 2026\", \"when\": \"w\", \"hl\": \"en\", \"gl\": \"us\"}}], \"sync_response_to_workbench\": false, \"current_step\": \"SEARCHING_AI_NEWS\", \"current_step_metric\": \"1/1 search\", \"thought\": \"Search for AI engineering tools news for JavaScript/TypeScript developers\", \"session_id\": \"kids\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"online/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v3.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781366442336,"responseId":"gen-1781366442-nVb9Cs9w3WfznKpCocsT"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"f4ce2ddba04b415a8f8f855b09667f6d","toolName":"composio__COMPOSIO_MULTI_EXECUTE_TOOL","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"data\":{\"results\":[{\"response\":{\"successful\":true,\"data\":{\"has_results\":false,\"news_results\":[],\"no_results_message\":\"No news articles found for query 'TypeScript JavaScript AI tools SDK libraries frontend developers 2026'. Suggestions: try removing or broadening the time filter (currently 'past week'); use fewer or more general keywords; try removing the country filter (currently 'us'). WARNING: Do not proceed with content generation without valid search results.\",\"query\":\"TypeScript JavaScript AI tools SDK libraries frontend developers 2026\",\"total_results\":null}},\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\",\"index\":0}],\"total_count\":1,\"success_count\":1,\"error_count\":0,\"session\":{\"id\":\"kids\",\"instructions\":\"REQUIRED: Pass session_id \\\"kids\\\" in ALL subsequent meta tool calls for this workflow.\"}},\"error\":null,\"log_id\":\"log_Fn5IU9mKOdCS\",\"successful\":true}"}],"details":{"mcpServer":"composio","mcpTool":"COMPOSIO_MULTI_EXECUTE_TOOL"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781366450544},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me try a broader search with different keywords and remove the time\n\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"4ed4f542477048dea2dbdf4d1f20bac5","name":"composio__COMPOSIO_MULTI_EXECUTE_TOOL","arguments":{"tools":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6},"sync_response_to_workbench":false,"current_step":"SEARCHING_AI_NEWS_BROADER","current_step_metric":"1/1 search","thought":"Broader search for AI development tools","session_id":"kids"},"partialArgs":"{\"tools\": [{\"tool_slug\": \"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\", \"arguments\": {\"query\": \"AI development tools JavaScript TypeScript\", \"hl\": \"en\", \"gl\": \"us\"}}], \"sync_response_to_workbench\": false, \"current_step\": \"SEARCHING_AI_NEWS_BROADER\", \"current_step_metric\": \"1/1 search\", \"thought\": \"Broader search for AI development tools\", \"session_id\": \"kids\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"online/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v3.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781366450548,"responseId":"gen-1781366450-d6dYCMUhVMhnH7LBbfyB"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"4ed4f542477048dea2dbdf4d1f20bac5","toolName":"composio__COMPOSIO_MULTI_EXECUTE_TOOL","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"data\":{\"results\":[{\"response\":{\"successful\":true,\"data\":{\"has_results\":true,\"news_results\":[{\"date\":\"3 weeks ago\",\"link\":\"https://www.csoonline.com/article/4176701/as-ai-speeds-coding-cve-lite-cli-keeps-security-deliberately-ai-free.html\",\"published_at\":\"2026-05-25 07:00:00 UTC\",\"snippet\":\"The OWASP-backed tool scans JavaScript and TypeScript lockfiles locally, aiming to help developers catch and remediate dependency risks...\",\"source\":\"CSO Online\",\"title\":\"As AI speeds coding, CVE Lite CLI keeps security deliberately AI-free\"},{\"date\":\"Dec 17, 2025\",\"link\":\"https://developers.googleblog.com/introducing-agent-development-kit-for-typescript-build-ai-agents-with-the-power-of-a-code-first-approach/\",\"published_at\":\"2025-12-17 08:00:00 UTC\",\"snippet\":\"Build powerful, autonomous multi-agent AI systems with Agent Development Kit (ADK) for TypeScript. A code-first, open-source framework.\",\"source\":\"blog.google\",\"title\":\"Introducing Agent Development Kit for TypeScript: Build AI Agents with the Power of a Code-First Approach\"},{\"date\":\"Jan 28, 2026\",\"link\":\"https://www.devclass.com/ai-ml/2026/01/28/typescript-inventor-anders-hejlsberg-ai-is-a-big-regurgitator-of-stuff-someone-has-done/4079582\",\"published_at\":\"2026-01-28 08:00:00 UTC\",\"snippet\":\"Microsoft technical fellow Anders Hejlsberg, inventor of both C# and TypeScript, said that existing languages are the ones […]\",\"source\":\"DevClass\",\"title\":\"TypeScript inventor Anders Hejlsberg: AI is 'a big regurgitator of stuff someone has done'\"},{\"date\":\"Mar 5, 2026\",\"link\":\"https://www.infoq.com/news/2026/03/ai-reshapes-language-choice/\",\"published_at\":\"2026-03-05 08:00:00 UTC\",\"snippet\":\"GitHub's Octoverse 2025 report reveals a \\\"convenience loop\\\" where AI coding assistants drive language choice. TypeScript's 66% surge to the...\",\"source\":\"infoq.com\",\"title\":\"GitHub Data Shows AI Tools Creating \\\"Convenience Loops\\\" That Reshape Developer Language Choices\"},{\"date\":\"Dec 21, 2025\",\"link\":\"https://devops.com/google-launches-agent-development-kit-for-typescript-a-code-first-approach-to-building-ai-agents/\",\"published_at\":\"2025-12-21 08:00:00 UTC\",\"snippet\":\"Google's new Agent Development Kit for TypeScript lets developers build AI agents using familiar tools and practices.\",\"source\":\"DevOps.com\",\"title\":\"Google Launches Agent Development Kit for TypeScript: A Code-First Approach to Building AI Agents\"},{\"date\":\"Oct 28, 2025\",\"link\":\"https://github.blog/news-insights/octoverse/octoverse-a-new-developer-joins-github-every-second-as-ai-leads-typescript-to-1/\",\"published_at\":\"2025-10-28 07:00:00 UTC\",\"snippet\":\"In this year's Octoverse, we uncover how AI, agents, and typed languages are driving the biggest shifts in software development in more than...\",\"source\":\"The GitHub Blog\",\"title\":\"Octoverse: A new developer joins GitHub every second as AI leads TypeScript to #1\"},{\"date\":\"Feb 5, 2026\",\"link\":\"https://www.infoworld.com/article/4127684/deno-sandbox-launched-for-running-ai-generated-code.html\",\"published_at\":\"2026-02-05 08:00:00 UTC\",\"snippet\":\"Deno Sandbox works in tandem with Deno Deploy—now in GA—to secure workloads where code must be generated, evaluated, or safely executed on...\",\"source\":\"InfoWorld\",\"title\":\"Deno Sandbox launched for running AI-generated code\"},{\"date\":\"Jan 15, 2026\",\"link\":\"https://www.techtarget.com/searchapparchitecture/tip/Why-did-TypeScript-become-GitHubs-fastest-growing-language\",\"published_at\":\"2026-01-15 08:00:00 UTC\",\"snippet\":\"Learn why TypeScript became the fastest growing programming language on GitHub and what that says about development at large.\",\"source\":\"TechTarget\",\"title\":\"Why did TypeScript become GitHub's fastest growing language?\"},{\"date\":\"Nov 11, 2025\",\"link\":\"https://eu.36kr.com/en/p/3549523189739394\",\"published_at\":\"2025-11-11 08:00:00 UTC\",\"snippet\":\"JavaScript closely follows. Java, C#, and PHP rank fourth, fifth, and sixth respectively, maintaining extremely stable rankings.\",\"source\":\"36 Kr\",\"title\":\"TypeScript Overtakes Python as Most Widely - Used Language on GitHub, Driven by AI\"},{\"date\":\"1 week ago\",\"link\":\"https://techgig.com/news/software-devops/cloudflare-acquires-voidzero-to-streamline-javascript-and-typescript-development/131530222\",\"published_at\":\"2026-06-05 11:25:13 UTC\",\"snippet\":\"Cloudflare has acquired VoidZero, a company focused on unified JavaScript and TypeScript development toolchains. This move aims to integrate...\",\"source\":\"techgig.com\",\"title\":\"Cloudflare Acquires VoidZero to Streamline JavaScript and TypeScript Development\"}],\"no_results_message\":null,\"query\":\"AI development tools JavaScript TypeScript\",\"total_results\":365}},\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\",\"index\":0}],\"total_count\":1,\"success_count\":1,\"error_count\":0,\"session\":{\"id\":\"kids\",\"instructions\":\"REQUIRED: Pass session_id \\\"kids\\\" in ALL subsequent meta tool calls for this workflow.\"}},\"error\":null,\"log_id\":\"log_kYJzXzmf6Yfo\",\"successful\":true}"}],"details":{"mcpServer":"composio","mcpTool":"COMPOSIO_MULTI_EXECUTE_TOOL"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781366458633},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Great! Now let me search for more specific AI tools and frameworks for frontend\n\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"19393143cac74424982fe6391d5506c9","name":"composio__COMPOSIO_MULTI_EXECUTE_TOOL","arguments":{"tools":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6},"sync_response_to_workbench":false,"current_step":"SEARCHING_FRONTEND_AI","current_step_metric":"1/1 search","tho